Raheem Sterling (Manchester City) and Teemu Pukki (Norwich) are already on four goals each with the 2019/2020 Premier League season only in its second week. Sterling scored a hat-trick in the 5-0 demolition of West Ham, before netting the first in their 2-2 draw with Tottenham Hotspur last weekend. Pukki grabbed a consolation as the Championship winners were humbled 4-1 by Liverpool in their opener, before helping himself to a hat-trick against Newcastle in the second fixture. Pierre Emerick Aubameyang (Arsenal), Ashley Barnes (Burnley), Marcus Rashford (Manchester United), Anthony Martial (Manchester United), Sergio Aguero (Manchester City) and Harry Kane (Tottenham Hotspur) are all on two goals each. The breakdown is as below: 4 goals: Raheem Sterling (Manchester City) and Teemu Pukki (Norwich) 2 goals: Pierre Emerick Aubameyang (Arsenal), Ashley Barnes (Burnley), Marcus Rashford (Manchester United), Anthony Martial (Manchester United), Sergio Aguero (Manchester City) and Harry Kane (Tottenham Hotspur) 1 goal: Sadio Mane, Roberto Firmino & Mohammed Salah (Liverpool), Tanguy Ndombele & Erik Lamela (Tottenham Hotspur) Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.